status_notes: The nature of weeping willows is to droop to the ground.  Rather than create work by continually prune trees that are healthy, we will examine the ground plane to determine what the proper ground treatment is for this condition.  Likely the area needs conversion from turf to mulch to further support the health of the trees.  It is not imperative that every foot of park land be accessible to people, in fact areas where people cannot access are some of the richest opportunities for wildlife.  Automatically pruning these trees is not the correct response.

status_notes: Custodians are sifting the sand daily. This is the extent of our sand area maintenance activities, other than replenishing sand when the levels get too low for safe fall protection. It is not possible to provide any assurance of safe, clean sand in an outdoor, uncovered sand box. Animals and people regularly use the sand in unintended ways, it is very easy for glass and other objects to be hidden under the sand and we do not have the staffing levels or equipment to do the kind of daily cleaning that would be needed to provide that assurance. We no longer recommend sand in play areas.
